Quickstart.exampleDescription: ddh is one function you can use for all your date manipulation needs.

ddh(some_string) takes a special string. "t" represents today (system timezone).
Strings can include specific dates, or adjustments/rules on dates as you will see below.
For more details, see the Ontology section.

Quickstart.exampleDescription:
ddh can read dates in a variety formats: e.g. MM/DD/YY, MM/DD/YYYY, M/D/YY, M/D/YYYY and more.
Default format is "Month First" (American convention), see Formats for alternatives.
Quickstart.defaultOutput: 07/02/1984

Quickstart.exampleDescription:
